	<H1>Applying for a Silver Fern Job Search visa</H1>
	
	
	
		<DIV class="textblock">
			<H2>Silver Fern Job Search Visa - 2014/2015 quota update</H2>
<P><IMG style="FLOAT: left" border="0" hspace="5" alt="No places available" vspace="5" src="/NR/rdonlyres/A9FAB418-115B-418F-ABF7-B4BEF096D634/0/WHSnoplacesavailable.jpg">The 2014/2015 Silver Fern Job Search category successfully opened&nbsp;on&nbsp;20 November 2014 and is now full. Further places will become available in&nbsp;November 2015.&nbsp;</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P>Further information about how to apply, can be found below. </P>
<H2>Applying for a Silver Fern Job Search visa</H2>
<P>The Silver Fern Job Search category is very popular and places are usually taken on the opening day.&nbsp;If you intend to apply, you must meet the requirements below. </P>
<H2>Meeting requirements for the Silver Fern Job Search visa </H2>
<P>Before you apply for a Silver Fern Job Search visa, you must:</P>
<UL>
<LI>not have previously been granted a Silver Fern Job Search visa 
<LI>be aged between 20 and 35 years of age inclusive 
<LI>be outside New Zealand during the application process 
<LI>hold a recognised bachelor&#8217;s degree or higher qualification, or a recognised trade qualification with a minimum of two years of work experience in that trade 
<LI>meet the <A title="Display definition of English language requirements in a new browser window" href="http://glossary.immigration.govt.nz/Englishlanguagerequirements.htm">English language requirements</A> set out for principal applicants under the Skilled Migrant Category (IELTS level 6.5) 
<LI>have a minimum of NZ$4,200 available funds to meet your living costs while you are in New Zealand 
<LI>meet our <A title="Display definition of health requirements for temporary entry to New Zealand" href="http://glossary.immigration.govt.nz/healthrequirementstemporary.htm">health</A> and <A title="Display definition of Good character in a new browser window" href="http://glossary.immigration.govt.nz/Goodcharacter.htm">character</A> requirements. </LI></UL>
<H2>Your qualifications </H2>
<P>The Silver Fern Job Search visa is for highly skilled people with recognised qualifications. You need to provide a New Zealand Qualifications Authority (NZQA) assessment &#8211; either an <A title="Display definition of Qualifications Assessment Report in a new browser window" href="http://glossary.immigration.govt.nz/QualificationsAssessmentReport.htm">International Qualification Assessment or a Qualifications Assessment Report</A> &#8211; of your qualification, unless one of the following applies: </P>
<UL>
<LI>Your qualification is on our <A title="Display definition of List of Qualifications Exempt from Assessment in a new browser window" href="http://glossary.immigration.govt.nz/listofrecognisedqualifications.htm">List of Qualifications Exempt from Assessment</A> 
<LI>You have <A title="Display definition of Registration (full or provisional) in a new browser window" href="http://glossary.immigration.govt.nz/RegFullOrProvisional.htm">full or provisional registration</A> and your qualification has been assessed by a <A href="http://www.immigration.govt.nz/migrant/stream/work/skilledmigrant/LinkAdministration/ToolboxLinks/registrationauthorities.htm">New Zealand registration authority</A> as being comparable to a New Zealand qualification on the List of Qualifications Exempt from Assessment.</LI></UL>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P>If your qualification is required for employment where <A href="http://www.immigration.govt.nz/migrant/stream/work/skilledmigrant/LinkAdministration/ToolboxLinks/occupationalregistration.htm" target="_blank">occupational registration</A> is required in New Zealand, you must show that you hold, or can obtain, full or provisional registration for that occupation in New Zealand.</P>
<H2>Tertiary qualification</H2>
<P>If you hold a tertiary qualification, you will need to show that it is equivalent to a New Zealand bachelor&#8217;s degree (level 7) or higher. </P>
<H2>Trade qualification</H2>
<P>If you hold a trade qualification, you will need to show that it is equivalent to a National Certificate (level 4) or a New Zealand Certificate (level 4) and that it is relevant to an occupation on part B or C of our list of skilled occupations. To check the list, see <A href="http://www.immigration.govt.nz/opsmanual/35165.htm" target="_blank">Appendix 6</A> in the Operational Manual. You will also need to show that you have two years&#8217; work experience that:</P>
<UL>
<LI>is relevant to your trade qualification 
<LI>has been gained in a <A title="Display definition of Comparable labour market in a new browser window" href="http://glossary.immigration.govt.nz/ComparableLabourMarket.htm">comparable labour market</A> to New Zealand 
<LI>has been gained after you completed your trade qualification (you cannot include work experience required as part of gaining your qualification) 
<LI>meets the additional requirements for <A title="Display definition of Recognised work experience in a new browser window" href="http://glossary.immigration.govt.nz/Recognisedworkexperience.htm">recognised work experience</A>. </LI></UL>
<H2>Health and character requirements</H2>
<P>You must meet health and character requirements that apply to people who intend to stay in New Zealand for a total of more than 24 months. This is because, on a Silver Fern Job Search visa, you intend to find long-term skilled employment. This requirement applies even if your visa is granted for a shorter time.</P>
<H2>Coming to New Zealand on a Silver Fern Job Search work visa</H2>
<P>The Silver Fern Job Search visa is valid for travel for six months from the date it is issued. Once you enter New Zealand, the Silver Fern Job Search visa allows you to stay for nine months from the date you arrive. You can travel and re-enter New Zealand during this time. </P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P>For more details, see the <A href="http://www.immigration.govt.nz/migrant/stream/work/silverfern/silverfernjobsearchfaqs.htm">Silver Fern Job Search: questions and answers</A>.</P></DIV>
